the marriage to make...

19:46.720 --> 19:49.849
<i>Will the parents of the
lost child in aisle seven</i>

19:49.920 --> 19:52.730
<i>Please come up
to the front and claim her?</i>

19:52.800 --> 19:54.165
<i>You're such a dick.</i>

19:54.240 --> 19:56.322
Oh, my God.

19:57.840 --> 20:00.207
<i>Bo was on a mission.</i>

20:00.280 --> 20:03.409
<i>He had to find the perfect
gift that would bring back his brother,</i>

20:03.480 --> 20:06.051
<i>who had become an alien
since his parents' divorce.</i>

20:17.480 --> 20:19.721
<i>That gift had to have
healing powers</i>

20:19.800 --> 20:21.882
<i>and it had to be cheap.</i>

20:28.000 --> 20:30.526
<i>He even sacrificed
his one-on-one with Santa.</i>

20:32.320 --> 20:34.209
<i>Nothing about this mission
was easy.</i>

20:34.280 --> 20:36.442
<i>But Bo would not be thwarted.</i>

20:37.600 --> 20:39.364
This is a whole
misunderstanding.

20:40.480 --> 20:42.244
Look, I'm somebody's mother.

20:42.320 --> 20:43.765
I have three kids.
They're teenagers.

20:43.840 --> 20:44.966
They're teenagers.

20:45.040 --> 20:47.646
Already, they don't
take me seriously.

20:47.720 --> 20:49.722
My husband's
an ethics professor.

20:49.800 --> 20:51.643
He'll never forgive me.

20:51.720 --> 20:54.371
My entire family is coming over at 5:00
for Christmas dinner,

20:54.480 --> 20:55.766
which I have to cook.

20:55.840 --> 20:58.889
Please. Don't you have
any compassion?

20:58.960 --> 21:00.564
So, it's all a misunderstanding?

21:00.640 --> 21:03.610
Yes.
Okay. So, clear it up.

21:03.680 --> 21:05.040
How'd the jewels
get in your mouth?

21:07.360 --> 21:08.691
Right. This way.

21:08.760 --> 21:09.921
I though it was a lozenge.

21:11.640 --> 21:13.927
<i>Shortly after his mother
moved out,</i>

21:14.040 --> 21:16.725
<i>Charlie felt as unclaimed
as a lost Christmas package,</i>

21:16.800 --> 21:18.882
<i>lying in the back corner
of the post office.</i>

21:20.000 --> 21:21.889
<i>In spite of this,</i>

21:21.960 --> 21:24.611
<i>he arrived at the mall,
vowing he would kiss Lauren Hesselberg,</i>

21:24.720 --> 21:26.961
<i>once and for all,
or die trying.</i>

21:55.720 --> 21:57.848
<i>Unnerved, he began
to watch himself.</i>

22:00.160 --> 22:02.401
<i>He told himself to coolly say,</i>

22:02.480 --> 22:05.165
<i>"What's up, Lauren?
What's up?"</i>

22:06.120 --> 22:07.360
Hey, Lauren.

22:10.520 --> 22:11.681
Hey, Charlie.

22:13.880 --> 22:15.041
What you doing here?

22:15.120 --> 22:16.531
I, I work here.

22:18.640 --> 22:20.483
Of course.

22:22.120 --> 22:23.929
<i>When, at last, he stood
in front of her,</i>

22:24.000 --> 22:26.571
