22:27.760 --> 22:29.285
<i>"Don't look at her boobs.</i>

22:30.640 --> 22:32.927
<i>"Do not look at her boobs."</i>

22:46.800 --> 22:49.929
I love the way Stewart does a little
food dance when his meal arrives.

22:52.000 --> 22:54.401
And how Sarah still puts
lipstick on for Hal.

22:57.080 --> 22:59.845
I like the way Paula Anderson
rests her breasts on the table,

22:59.920 --> 23:01.285
as if they were tired.

23:03.920 --> 23:08.926
We were so sad to see you go,
Ruby. I'm gonna miss you.

23:12.440 --> 23:13.566
Take care, okay?

23:13.640 --> 23:15.244
- Merry Christmas.
- Bye, guys.

23:15.320 --> 23:16.924
You're going somewhere?

23:22.280 --> 23:23.406
It's my last day.

23:25.120 --> 23:27.282
What?
Yeah.

23:27.360 --> 23:30.250
You tell the lady with the lipstick on
her teeth and you don't tell me?

23:30.320 --> 23:32.561
I don't...
I didn't know how to tell you.

23:34.840 --> 23:37.081
It's like that movie you gave
me, <i>Born Yesterday,</i> right,

23:37.160 --> 23:39.731
when Billie Dawn walks
out on Harry Brock.

23:39.800 --> 23:42.007
There's a better
kind of life than the one I got.

23:43.600 --> 23:46.365
You told me,
right here, you said,

23:46.440 --> 23:50.126
"Starting over, you could
be the hero of your own life."

23:50.240 --> 23:51.685
You can be a hero, here.

23:51.760 --> 23:54.491
Where are you going?

23:54.560 --> 23:56.130
Hot Coffee, Mississippi.

23:56.200 --> 23:58.168
I found it on a map
when I was 14 years old.

23:58.240 --> 24:01.005
It seems like the perfect place
for a waitress.

24:01.080 --> 24:03.048
Look, I don't understand.
I'm confused.

24:03.120 --> 24:06.886
You've never even been there.
It's the worst idea I've ever heard of.

24:06.960 --> 24:10.169
But I... I want to start over.
I need...

24:10.920 --> 24:12.331
I need a change.

24:12.400 --> 24:14.767
No, no, no, no.
Leaving doesn't change anything.

24:14.840 --> 24:16.490
Everything just
comes with you.

24:16.600 --> 24:18.045
Hot Coffee, Mississippi?

24:18.120 --> 24:20.202
That's a place?
It's like a line from a sitcom.

24:20.280 --> 24:21.725
Bucky.

24:21.800 --> 24:23.802
You're a bird watcher.
You watch us all from a distance.

24:23.880 --> 24:25.723
We're just characters
that amuse you.

24:25.800 --> 24:28.406
Not true.
You love everybody at arm's length,

24:28.480 --> 24:30.323
keep it up and you'll
end up alone, Ruby.

24:30.400 --> 24:32.129
That's a terrible thing
to say to me.

24:32.240 --> 24:33.605
Well, it's a terrible
thing to watch.

24:33.680 --> 24:35.091
It's very cowardly.

24:35.200 --> 24:37.646
So, in other words,
you think that I'm a coward.

24:37.720 --> 24:41.122
No. Not in other words,
those are the words.

24:41.200 --> 24:43.680
You think you can run away,
hiding in Hot Chocolate?

24:43.760 --> 24:45.444
You're a coward.

24:45.520 --> 24:46.646
You can pay up front.

24:50.040 --> 24:52.960
You tell everybody at the restaurant
you're leaving and you don't tell me.

25:37.280 --> 25:38.486
May I ask you something?

25:43.640 --> 25:46.211
Is this something that they teach
you at the Police Academy?

25:46.280 --> 25:48.044
Or have you always
been a robot?

25:49.240 --> 25:51.368
I can understand

25:51.440 --> 25:53.488
that you need
professional distance

25:53.560 --> 25:55.130
from a hardened criminal.

25:55.240 --> 25:59.723
But when there's a poor,
downtrodden housewife,

25:59.800 --> 26:02.451
sobbing in the back
of your car on Christmas,

26:02.520 --> 26:04.124
one has to wonder.

26:07.440 --> 26:09.283
I'm guessing it's something
they teach you.

26:10.800 --> 26:12.689
No one's born that way.

26:12.800 --> 26:15.087
<i>Though Officer Williams never
engaged with suspects</i>

26:15.160 --> 26:16.366
<i>in the back of his car,</i>

26:16.440 --> 26:18.522
<i>Emma unknowingly
pierced his armor.</i>

26:19.760 --> 26:21.250
I'm not a robot.

26:24.040 --> 26:25.201
What?

26:25.280 --> 26:27.328
I have feelings, just
like everyone else.

26:29.520 --> 26:30.965
Would you like
to talk about it?

26:31.040 --> 26:32.530
I'm not talking to you.

26:32.600 --> 26:34.489
Take me to your leader.
Shut up.

26:35.840 --> 26:38.081
Listen.

26:38.200 --> 26:41.921
You landed in a pot of jam,
arresting me.

26:42.000 --> 26:45.561
I've been a doctor
for 20 years.

26:45.640 --> 26:47.961
People pay me a lot
to listen to their problems.

26:52.880 --> 26:55.611
You're a head-shrinker?

26:55.680 --> 26:58.160
<i>What Emma did not know
was that Officer Williams</i>

26:58.240 --> 27:00.129
had once sought out counseling,

27:00.200 --> 27:02.965
<i>but couldn't get over the fact
that he would have to talk.</i>

27:09.960 --> 27:14.761
And we're off, with Rudolph,
right here, to see Santa.

27:14.840 --> 27:16.604
And Donner, and Vixen...

27:16.680 --> 27:18.682
And Blitzen and Nixon...

27:21.600 --> 27:23.170
Look at this.
It's beautiful.

27:33.960 --> 27:36.691
Silent Night <i>reminded
Charlotte of a part of herself</i>

27:36.800 --> 27:40.122
<i>that now felt inescapably
out of her grasp.</i>

27:40.200 --> 27:43.841
<i>She caroled to deflect
the fact that she missed that person...</i>

27:43.920 --> 27:45.604
<i>as much as Sam did.</i>

27:45.680 --> 27:50.481
<i>♪ All is bright</i>

27:50.560 --> 27:54.849
<i>♪ Brown young virgin</i>

27:54.920 --> 27:57.605
<i>♪ Mother and child... ♪</i>

27:57.680 --> 27:59.170
What?

27:59.280 --> 28:01.089
